cs.CG, cs.NA, cs.DS, cs.GR, cs.SI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper deals with geometry processing and shape analysis. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of numerical methods such as the boundary element method and hierarchical numerical schemes. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possibility as the paper may involve the development of algorithms for solving eigenvalue and linear problems on large-scale meshes. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is another possibility as the paper may involve the visualization of shapes and geometry. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is less likely but still a possibility as the paper may involve the analysis of networks or graphs derived from shapes.
